---
title: Shawarma Spiced Pork with Couscous and Peas
description: Traditional shawarma is grilled on a spit for hours (or even days). We’re speeding up that process by letting the spices do the talking. Here, pork tenderloin is rubbed in our signature shawarma spice blend, which is full of cumin, coriander, and other warm aromatics. Then it’s seared in a pan until nice and crusty and served on a fluffy bed of couscous with peas.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w22-r4-108d3c63.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w22-r4-852406e5.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/shawarma-spiced-pork-58f0ce7c2310a816210ceea2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 530 kcal
  fat: 12 g
  saturated fat: 3.5 g
  carbohydrates: 55 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 52 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 380 mg
servings: 2
cuisine: Middle East
author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Halve, peel, and dice
@yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced). Pick leaves from @cilantro{1/4}(leaves
picked, discarded stems). Roughly chop leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
onion and cook, tossing, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in
@chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{3/4%cup} and bring to a boil. Add
@couscous{1/2} and cover, and remove from heat.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season
@pork tenderloin{12} all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the
@shawarma spice blend{1}. Sear in pan until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.
Transfer pan to oven.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, place pork on a baking sheet.

Roast until pork reaches desired doneness, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mince or grate @garlic{1}(minced) until you have 1/2 tsp (you may
have a clove left over). Halve @lemon{1}. In a #small bowl{}, combine
@yogurt{1}, remaining shawarma spice, a squeeze of lemon, and a pinch of
garlic. Stir in @water{1%TBSP} to give mixture a saucy consistency. Season with
salt, pepper, and more garlic (to taste).

Once pork is done, remove from pan and let rest ~{5%minutes}. Place pan used
for pork over low heat. Add @peas{4} and toss until heated through,
~{1-2%minutes}. Fluff couscous with a #fork{}, then add to pan along with a
squeeze of lemon and toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice pork. Divide couscous mixture between plates, then top with pork.
Dollop with yogurt sauce and garnish with cilantro.